{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb406d2be-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s91"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"91"},"text":"§ 91.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Extending time for entry of vessels subject to quarantine","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of Health and Human Services is authorized, whenever a conformity to such quarantines and health laws requires it, and in respect to vessels subject thereto, to prolong the terms limited for the entry of the same, and the report or entry of their cargoes, and to vary or dispense with any other regulations applicable to such reports or entries. No part of the cargo of any vessel shall, however, in any case, be taken out or unladen therefrom, otherwise than is allowed by law, or according to the regulations established by sections 88 and 90 of this title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb406d2bf-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(R.S. § 4796; 1939 Reorg. Plan No. I, § 201, eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1939-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1939","children":[],"tail":", 4 F.R. 2728, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/53/1424"},"text":"53 Stat. 1424","children":[],"tail":"; 1953 Reorg. Plan No. 1, §§ 5, 8, eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1953-04-11"},"text":"Apr. 11, 1953","children":[],"tail":", 18 F.R. 2053, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/67/631"},"text":"67 Stat. 631","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/88/tV/s509/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–88, title V, § 509(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1979","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/93/695"},"text":"93 Stat. 695","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb406d2c0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb406d2c1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idb406d2c2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"R.S. § 4796 derived from ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1799-02-23/ch12/s1"},"text":"act Feb. 23, 1799, ch. 12, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/1/619"},"text":"1 Stat. 619","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb406d2c3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"idb406d2c4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“Secretary of Health and Human Services” substituted in text for “Secretary of Health, Education, and Welfare” pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/88/s509/b"},"text":"section 509(b) of Pub. L. 96–88","children":[],"tail":", which is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s3508/b"},"text":"section 3508(b) of Title 20","children":[],"tail":", Education."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"idb406d2c5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"idb406d2c6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Functions of Federal Security Administrator transferred to Secretary of Health, Education, and Welfare and all agencies of Federal Security Agency transferred to Department of Health, Education and Welfare by section 5 of 1953 Reorg. Plan No. 1 of 1953, set out as a note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s3501"},"text":"section 3501 of this title","children":[],"tail":". Federal Security Agency and office of Administrator abolished by section 8 of Reorg. Plan No. 1 of 1953."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Functions of Department of the Treasury relating to public health transferred to Federal Security Agency pursuant to Reorg. Plan No. I of 1939, set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
